# GDScript Conventions

- Tabs for indentation (not spaces)
- PascalCase scene files: `CombatManager.tscn`, `DeckViewer.tscn`
- camelCase variables and functions
- Use `GlobalEnums` for shared enums — do not redefine locally
- Resources: `CardData`, `Effect`, `EnemyData`, `EnemyMove`, `RelicData`

## Scene patterns

- `DeckViewer`, `TopBar`, `EscapeMenu` are CanvasLayers — call `init()` **before** `add_child`
- `RunState._ready()` spawns TopBar and EscapeMenu via `call_deferred`
- Scene history: write on combat/map/reward/shop/rest/lore; skip main menu and lose screen

## Combat tree

```
CombatManager → DeckManager, UI/UIHeirarchy
  → BattleArea (PlayerArea + SummonContainer, EnemyArea)
  → BottomBar (hand, energy, end turn)
```

## Summon rules (decided)

- One summon instance per card at a time
- Card returns to discard when summon dies
- Click summon to activate (separate from card selection)
- Used summons grey out; reset at turn start
- `summon_hp`, `takes_aggro`, `is_passive`, `summon_damage` on CardData
